reviewText: Refreshing to watch a political discussion and not a yelling competition.
What a great mind she had and what vision she showed in response to her opposition.  No wonder they are all so happy she is no longer with us.
Where else could you find so conviently this historically significant exchange between two of the great conservative intellects of Twentieth Century.
excellent clarity from Margaret and as always job well done from our William F. Buckley Jr. and so happy to own it
This shows the differences of European and American conservatism.  You also get a sense of the greatness of this iconic lady.
